<div id="review_3705898726" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3705898726" />
    <a title="Matt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31667052-matt"><img alt="Matt" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1589658539p2/31667052.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3705898726?book_show_action=true">Dec 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matt" href="/user/show/31667052-matt">Matt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781411432024" href="/book/show/7541214-cyrano-de-bergerac">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3705898726&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3705898726" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3361404718234542224">Cyrano de Bergerac is a story of mischanced and unrequited love. <br/><br/>This is a classic French play - everyone knows about Cyrano’s big nose which he believes makes him ugly to Roxane. Cyrano has all the other attributes Roxane wants, but that one feature of his big old nose 👃🏻 holds him back from his heart’s desire. Perhaps a lesson to be taken from this is to try to put yourself out there more - you may not always get what you want, but you won’t know if you don’t go for it. <br/><br/>I actually didn’t know </span>
  <span id="freeText3361404718234542224" style="display:none">Cyrano de Bergerac is a story of mischanced and unrequited love. <br /><br />This is a classic French play - everyone knows about Cyrano’s big nose which he believes makes him ugly to Roxane. Cyrano has all the other attributes Roxane wants, but that one feature of his big old nose 👃🏻 holds him back from his heart’s desire. Perhaps a lesson to be taken from this is to try to put yourself out there more - you may not always get what you want, but you won’t know if you don’t go for it. <br /><br />I actually didn’t know until I picked this up that it was a play - I thought it was a short novel. I’ve read other reviews that the five different acts felt disjointed and I agree. I’m sure it plays out well on the stage, but it was a bit hard to follow and to get into it. <br /><br />I’m thankful this came up as a GR group buddy read. It was something different and light for this time of year which is what I needed as I’m winding up my 2020 reading year. 3 stars. I’ll probably revisit it again at some point. <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3361404718234542224" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


