<div id="review_3498801638" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3498801638" />
    <a title="Eye of Sauron" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/61597976-eye-of-sauron"><img alt="Eye of Sauron" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1479408483p2/61597976.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3498801638?book_show_action=true">Aug 16, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eye of Sauron" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eye of Sauron" href="/user/show/61597976-eye-of-sauron">Eye of Sauron</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781593083878" href="/book/show/2893607-cyrano-de-bergerac">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/61597976-eye-of-sauron?shelf=plays">plays</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/61597976-eye-of-sauron?shelf=top-25-plays">top-25-plays</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/61597976-eye-of-sauron?shelf=top-100-plays">top-100-plays</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/61597976-eye-of-sauron?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3498801638" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9420891393586746732">Being thoroughly versed in Shakespeare and essentially ignorant of all other playwrights, reading <i>Cyrano</i> was an odd experience - like Shakespeare got a little bolder and more exciting while having an identity crisis. This play doesn&apos;t quite know if it&apos;s a comedy or a tragedy - it reads like the former, while the actual plot seems like the latter. That struck me as a faux pas, but it could very well be acceptable and I would have no idea.<br/><br/><a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[My actual problem with this weird dichotomy </span></span>
  <span id="freeText9420891393586746732" style="display:none">Being thoroughly versed in Shakespeare and essentially ignorant of all other playwrights, reading <i>Cyrano</i> was an odd experience - like Shakespeare got a little bolder and more exciting while having an identity crisis. This play doesn't quite know if it's a comedy or a tragedy - it reads like the former, while the actual plot seems like the latter. That struck me as a faux pas, but it could very well be acceptable and I would have no idea.<br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[My actual problem with this weird dichotomy is the ending. The play feels like a comedy the entire time, and it does quite a good job at making you believe everything's going to work out beautifully for everyone involved. It's also quite funny, which helps the case for the comedy. The <b>ending</b>, however, comes out of nowhere and smashes these hopes to Jupiter, unrepentantly saying <i>you know, I think this'll be a tragedy after all</i>. And that irritated me. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />Overall, however, I really did enjoy this play. Definitely one of the best non-Shakespearean plays I've read, and just a lot of fun. I would love to see this in theaters, but they're all closed... perhaps I'll watch the movie instead.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9420891393586746732" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


